@notice Withdraws W2R tokens from the contract to the owner's address.
 @param amount The amount of W2R tokens to be withdrawn.

devdoc.details: The contract uses OpenZeppelin's SafeERC20, Ownable, and IERC20 contracts.

params._w2rToken: The address of the W2R token contract.

params.amount: The amount of W2R tokens to be distributed.

returns._0: A boolean value indicating whether the contract is approved.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._lenderContractOwner: The address of the lender contract owner
params._renterContract: The address of the renter contract
params._renterContractOwner: The address of the renter contract owner

params.contractAddress: The address of the contract to be removed.

returns._0: A boolean value indicating whether the contract was successfully removed.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._sentToLender: Set to true if deposit is to be sent to the lender, false if it is to be sent to the renter. This function is only callable by the owner of the contract. It first checks if the lender address is not zero and if the deposit has not been sent yet. Then it checks if the deposit exists and updates the deposit status based on the _sentToLender parameter. Finally, it updates the totalDepositsWhenDestroyed and transfers the deposit amount to the appropriate recipient.

params.contractAddress: The address of the contract to be approved or disapproved.
params.status: The approval status to be set, true for approved and false for disapproved.

params._whitelistLenders: The address of the WhitelistLenders contract.

params._whitelistRenters: The address of the WhitelistRenters contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.amount: The amount of W2R tokens to be withdrawn.

distributeW2R(address,uint256).notice: Distributes W2R tokens to a specified receiver.

getApprovedContract(address).notice: Gets the approval status of a contract address.

receiveDepositsWhenDestroyed(address,add.notice: A bikeShare contract can be destroyed after 2 days since the end of the rental period, or immediately if there is no rental The wait of 2 days is to give the renter time to return bike in case of delay or dispute After this time, if the lender has not received the bike and want to destroy the bikeShare contract, deposit will be placed here.It's not mandatory to destroy the bikeShare contract, it's in case the lender wants to destroy it: deposit must be saved umtil the dispute is resolved

sentDeposit(address,bool).notice: Send deposit to either lender or renter.

setApprovedContract(address,bool).notice: Approves or disapproves a contract address.

withdrawW2R(uint256).notice: Withdraws W2R tokens from the contract to the owner's address.

userdoc.notice: This contract serves as a vault for managing the distribution and withdrawal of W2R tokens.
